<p class="">    <h2>Key Challenges in the Maternity Pajamas Market</h2>    <ul>        <li>            <strong>Limited Variety:</strong> The maternity pajamas market faces challenges due to a             <em>limited variety</em> of styles and designs. Pregnant women seek options that are both             <em>fashionable</em> and <em>comfortable</em>, but many brands fail to provide diverse choices             that cater to different tastes and preferences.        </li>        <li>            <strong>Size Inclusivity:</strong> Many manufacturers do not offer a full range of sizes,             which can alienate potential customers. The lack of <em>size inclusivity</em> can lead to             <em>frustration</em> among expecting mothers who struggle to find well-fitting pajamas during             their pregnancy.        </li>        <li>            <strong>Quality vs. Price:</strong> Striking a balance between <em>quality</em> and price             remains a significant challenge. While consumers want affordable options, they also expect             high-quality materials that provide lasting comfort. This <em>price sensitivity</em> can lead             to compromised quality, creating dissatisfaction.        </li>        <li>            <strong>Market Awareness:</strong> There is often a <em>lack of awareness</em> about the             importance of comfortable sleepwear during pregnancy. Many expectant mothers may not prioritize             investing in specialized maternity pajamas, viewing them as a luxury rather than a necessity.         </li>        <li>            <strong>Environmental Concerns:</strong> With a growing emphasis on sustainability,             consumers are increasingly demanding <em>eco-friendly</em> options. The maternity pajamas             market must adapt to this trend by incorporating sustainable fabrics and ethical production             methods.        </li>    </ul>    <h2>Potential Growth Opportunities in the Maternity Pajamas Market<